<module>
  <title>a(i)n-</title>
  <p><strong>a(i)n-</strong> is a negative or intensifying compounding prefix.</p>
  <hr/>
  <p><strong>ain-</strong> as <a href="?xx=nouns/compound_common_nouns">noun-compounding</a> prefix –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>ceàrd</i> <en>metalsmith</en> ⇒ <m>aincheard</m> <en>buffoon</en></li>
    <li><i>ceist</i> <en>question</en> ⇒ <m>aincheist</m> <en>puzzle, riddle</en></li>
    <li><i>cinealtas</i> <en>clannishness</en> ⇒ <m>ainchinealtas</m> <en>racism</en> (cf. <i>ainchinealtach</i> <en>racist</en>)</li>
    <li><i>deòin</i> <en>assent, will</en> ⇒ <m>aindeoin</m> <en>reluctance</en></li>
    <li><i>dlighe</i> <en>godly, religious</en> ⇒ <m>ain-dlighe</m> <en>injustice</en> (also <i>aindlighe</i>, cf. <i>mì-dhligheach</i> <en>illegal</en>)</li>
    <li><i>eòl</i> <en>knowledge</en> ⇒ <m>aineol</m> <en>foreigner, stranger, unfamiliarity, strangeness</en></li>
    <li><i>fiach</i> <en>value, debt</en> ⇒ <m>ainfhiach</m> <en>debt</en></li>
    <li><i>fios</i> <en>knowledge</en> ⇒ <m>ainfhios</m> <en>ignorance</en></li>
    <li><i>mèin</i> <en>character, disposition</en> ⇒ <m>ain-mèin</m> <en>fury, rage</en> (also <i>ainmein</i>, <i>ain-mèinn</i>)</li>
    <li><i>neart</i> <en>strength</en> ⇒ <m>ainneart</m> <en>violence</en></li>
    <li><i>riaghailt</i> <en>rule, government</en> ⇒ <m>ain-riaghailt</m> <en>anarchy</en> (also <i>mì-riaghailt</i> <en>chaos, misrule</en>)</li>
    <li><i>teas</i> <en>heat</en> ⇒ <m>ainteas</m> <en>inflammation, fervour</en></li>
    <li><i>tighearna</i> <en>lord</en> ⇒ <m>aintighearna</m> <en>despot, tyrant</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>aim-</strong> as <a href="?xx=nouns/compound_common_nouns">noun-compounding</a> prefix –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>beart</i> <en>instrument, fact</en> ⇒ <m>aimbeart</m> <en>need, necessity</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>aimh-</strong> as <a href="?xx=nouns/compound_common_nouns">noun-compounding</a> prefix –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>leas</i> <en>advantage, benefit</en> ⇒ <m>aimhleas</m> <en>mischief</en></li>
    <li><i>riar</i> <en>will, inclination</en> ⇒ <m>aimhriar</m> <en>inconsistency</en> (also <i>aimh-rèir</i>)</li>
    <li><i>rèite</i> <en>agreement</en> ⇒ <m>aimhreit</m> <en>discord, unrest</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>ain-</strong> as <a href="?xx=adjectives/compound_adjectives">adjective-compounding</a> prefix –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>diadhaidh</i> <en>godly, religious</en> ⇒ <m>ain-diadhaidh</m> <en>godless, irreligious</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>aimh-</strong> as <a href="?xx=adjectives/compound_adjectives">adjective-compounding</a> prefix –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>leathann</i> <en>broad, wide</en> ⇒ <m>aimhleathann</m> <en>narrow</en></li>
  </ul>
